{#-
  Weekly Argosy digest — plain-text fallback (Spec E commit #8 §7.1).

  Shipped alongside the HTML body as the second alternative in the
  multipart/alternative SMTP envelope. Clients that don't render HTML
  (text-only mail readers, accessibility tools, spam-filter previews)
  read this version.

  Same secrets-hygiene contract as the HTML template: NO tokens, API
  keys, VAPID secrets, admin tokens. User-supplied LLM text is rendered
  with default autoescape via the Jinja environment (autoescape is
  off-by-default in plain-text but our environment enables it for both
  .html.j2 and .txt.j2 templates so we get consistent rendering — the
  scanner test asserts no secret-shaped string sneaks through).
-#}
